# Blueprint Builder — Phased Implementation Plan

> A guided, visual, searchable builder that enables users to create complete project blueprints by selecting options, generating structured project documentation.

---

## Project Summary

Blueprint Builder is the core module of the Project Builder platform. Users select a project type (website, web app, mobile app, API, etc.), answer guided questions, choose technologies/features/integrations, get AI recommendations, validate their configuration, and generate complete project documentation (PRD, README, API spec, etc.).

The PRD defines **8 architectural engines**, **6 builder categories**, **11 generated outputs**, and a rich UI with left nav, main panel, right summary panel, search bar, progress indicator, and AI assistant panel.

---

## Technology Stack Decision

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Please confirm the tech stack before we begin.** Based on the PRD's complexity (dynamic question engine, search, AI, auto-save, multiple engines), I recommend:

| Layer | Recommendation | Rationale |
|-------|---------------|-----------|
| **Framework** | **Next.js 15 (App Router)** | SSR for SEO, file-based routing, API routes for AI calls |
| **Language** | **TypeScript** | Type safety critical for complex data models |
| **Styling** | **Vanilla CSS** (per workspace rules) | Full control, no dependency |
| **State Management** | **Zustand** | Lightweight, supports auto-save, undo/redo |
| **Database** | **Supabase (PostgreSQL)** | Auth, storage, realtime — aligns with PRD integrations |
| **AI** | **OpenAI / Anthropic API** | For recommendations, descriptions, explanations |
| **Search** | **Client-side fuzzy search (Fuse.js)** | Fast instant search over option library |
| **Export** | **jsPDF + file-saver** | PDF/Markdown/JSON export |

> [!NOTE]
> If you prefer a different stack (e.g., Vite + React, or a backend-less approach with localStorage), let me know and I'll adjust the plan.

