## Phase 1: Foundation & Core UI Shell

**Goal:** Project scaffolding, data models, design system, and the main layout shell.

### [NEW] Project Scaffolding
- Initialize Next.js 15 project with TypeScript
- Configure project structure: `/app`, `/components`, `/lib`, `/data`, `/types`, `/stores`
- Set up CSS design system (colors, typography, spacing, animations)

### [NEW] `types/blueprint.ts`
Core TypeScript interfaces:
- `Blueprint` — top-level project data container
- `ProjectType` — enum for Website, Web App, Android, iOS, Desktop, API, etc.
- `ProjectBasics` — name, description, category, industry, audience, business model
- `TechnologySelection` — frontend, backend, database, hosting, etc.
- `FeatureSelection` — auth, dashboard, payments, etc.
- `IntegrationSelection` — Stripe, Firebase, Supabase, etc.
- `QualityConfig` — security, performance, SEO, testing, deployment
- `BuilderSection` — metadata for each builder category
- `Option` — universal option structure (name, description, advantages, limitations, compatible techs, alternatives, difficulty, popularity, recommendation score, tags, docs link)
- `ValidationResult`, `Recommendation`

### [NEW] `stores/blueprintStore.ts`
Zustand store with:
- Blueprint state (all sections)
- Actions: `setProjectBasics`, `addTechnology`, `removeTechnology`, `addFeature`, `toggleIntegration`, etc.
- Undo/redo history stack
- Computed: completion percentage, validation status

### [NEW] Core Layout Components
- `BuilderLayout` — 3-panel layout (left nav, main, right summary)
- `LeftNavigation` — category list with completion indicators
- `MainPanel` — renders active section
- `RightSummaryPanel` — live project summary
- `ProgressBar` — completion percentage
- `StickyActionBar` — Save, Next, Back, Generate buttons

### Deliverables
- Running app with 3-panel layout
- Navigation between empty section placeholders
- Type-safe data model
- Design system with premium aesthetics (dark mode, gradients, glassmorphism)

