## Phase 3: Search, Progress & Validation

**Goal:** Instant search across all options, progress tracking, and configuration validation.

### [NEW] `lib/searchEngine.ts`
- Fuse.js integration for fuzzy search across all options
- Category filtering, tag filtering
- Recently used tracking (localStorage)
- Favorites system
- Keyboard shortcut support (Cmd/Ctrl+K to open search)

### [NEW] `components/SearchModal.tsx`
- Command palette style search modal
- Instant results with category badges
- Keyboard navigation
- Filter chips for categories/tags
- Popular options section

### [NEW] `lib/progressEngine.ts`
- Calculate completion percentage per section and overall
- Track completed vs remaining sections
- Identify required actions
- Return validation status per section

### [NEW] `lib/validationEngine.ts`
- `validateBlueprint(blueprint)` → `ValidationResult[]`
- Rules: missing required fields, conflicting selections (e.g., iOS + Windows Desktop hosting), unsupported combinations, empty categories, security warnings, performance risks
- Clear error messages with fix suggestions
- Severity levels: error, warning, info

### [NEW] `components/ValidationPanel.tsx`
- Shows validation results grouped by severity
- Click-to-fix: jumps to the relevant section
- Real-time validation as user makes changes

### Deliverables
- Working search with fuzzy matching
- Live progress bar with section-level detail
- Validation that catches real configuration issues
- Keyboard shortcuts

