## Phase 5: AI Recommendations & Assistant

**Goal:** Smart recommendations and an AI assistant panel.

### [NEW] `lib/recommendationEngine.ts`
- Rule-based recommendations (no AI dependency):
  - Compatible technologies (Next.js → Tailwind, Vercel, Prisma)
  - Missing features (auth selected but no security config)
  - Security improvements
  - Performance improvements
  - Accessibility improvements
  - Common integrations for selected stack
- Recommendation scoring and prioritization

### [NEW] `lib/aiAssistant.ts`
- API route for AI calls (`/api/ai/recommend`, `/api/ai/explain`, `/api/ai/describe`)
- AI-powered: explain options, suggest architecture, estimate complexity, generate descriptions
- Graceful fallback if AI unavailable

### [NEW] `components/AIAssistantPanel.tsx`
- Slide-out panel on the right
- Chat-like interface for asking questions about options
- Contextual recommendations based on current section
- "Why this recommendation?" explanations
- Never silently changes selections (per PRD §16)

### [NEW] `components/RecommendationBadge.tsx`
- Inline recommendation badges on option cards
- "Recommended for your stack" indicators
- Compatibility scores

### Deliverables
- Rule-based recommendations working without AI
- AI assistant panel for explanations and suggestions
- Contextual recommendations per section
- Recommendation badges on option cards

